2 : site context


The site between the Sun Palace transport station, the greenbelt 
and  the  Bahe  River  serves  as  threshold  between  urban  and 
rural  life.  The  old  rice  paddy  proportions,  creating  a  plan  of 
ribbons  cut  transversely  by  irrigation  canals,  determined  the 
physical  form  of  the  village.    Today,  this  form  is  still  evident  in 
the  housing  dimensions  and  the  irrigation  canals  now  serve  as 
primary streets. 

